reason.tex:
%text If $f(x)$ be things like $x^2 - 7x + 89$ or $x^5-26x$, that is, a polynomial, then \[ \lim_{x\to a}f(x) = f(a) \].
Hence, $\lim_{x\to 1}f(x)$ for the two polynomials above would be as follows
% \begin{tabular}{|c|c|} \hline f(x) & \lim_{x\to 1}f(x) = f(1) \\ \hline x^2-7x+89 & \lim_{x\to 1}(x^2-7x+89) = 83 \\ \hline x^5-26x& \lim_{x\to 1}(x^5-26x)= -25 \\ \hline \end{tabular}
